Kisii governor aspirant and South Mugirango MP Manson Nyamweya has welcomed the move by opposition leaders to form a super alliance in a bid to unseat President Uhuru Kenyatta.&ldquo;The country can only progress through good leadership, which Jubilee has failed to show. The President is turning a blind eye to corruption,&rdquo; he said. Nyamweya spoke in Tabaka ward on Friday during the burial of resident Mary Obai.He said the Jubilee government has done little since 2013. Nyamweya urged opposition leaders to agree on who will be the flagbearer to avoid confusion. He said NASA is &ldquo;the only sure way to defeat Uhuru&rdquo;.